You have 2 separate issues.

## 1. Callback test: `authResult` is null

Your mock is probably not matching because the controller calls:

```java
authService.handleCallback(code, state)
```

Use this, no `eq()`:

```java
when(authService.handleCallback(anyString(), anyString()))
        .thenReturn(new AuthResult("session-123", "B2BOOST_BE"));
```

Then verify:

```java
verify(authService).handleCallback("auth-code", "state-123");
```

## 2. Exchange test: JSON is snake_case

Actual response:

```json
{
  "user_id": "testuser",
  "selected_sales_point_id": "SP001"
}
```

So change assertions from camelCase:

```java
jsonPath("$.userId")
```

to snake_case:

```java
.andExpect(jsonPath("$.user_id").value("testuser"))
.andExpect(jsonPath("$.username").value("testuser"))
.andExpect(jsonPath("$.email").value("test@test.com"))
.andExpect(jsonPath("$.roles[0]").value("SELLER"))
.andExpect(jsonPath("$.app_id").value("B2BOOST_BE"))
.andExpect(jsonPath("$.selected_sales_point_id").value("SP001"))
.andExpect(jsonPath("$.selected_org_unit_id").value("ORG001"));
```

For missing appId, because your global handler returns 500 for now, either update the expectation to 500 or better add this in `GlobalExceptionHandler`:

```java
@ExceptionHandler(IllegalArgumentException.class)
@ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST)
public Map<String, String> handleIllegalArgumentException(IllegalArgumentException ex) {
    return Map.of("message", ex.getMessage());
}
```

Then the test can stay:

```java
.andExpect(status().isBadRequest());
```
